<div class="content" name="Introduction" uuid="0f2ef67f-7237-48ed-bc68-d4c43cf62809"><p>The Remote Procedure Call Location Services Extensions is a
legacy protocol that has been deprecated and is not used by Microsoft.
Implementers should use the DCE-based RPC Location Services capabilities in <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=89824" data-linktype="external">[C706]</a>.</p><p>The Remote Procedure Call Location Services Extensions is a
set of extensions/restrictions to the distributed computing environment (DCE)
remote procedure call (RPC) Location Services specified in [C706]. These
extensions add new capabilities to the DCE RPC Location Services Protocol.</p><p>This document specifies a set of extensions and restrictions
to the DCE RPC Location Services specification as specified in [C706].</p><p>Sections 1.5, 1.8, 1.9, 2, and 3 of this specification are
normative. All other sections and examples in this specification are
informative.</p></div>